cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as word sense disambiguation, machine translation, and lexical substitution. The use of bidirectional LSTMs to compute context-sensitive word representations is a common technique in this field. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Learning) as the paper focuses on learning representations of words in context using neural networks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to learn the parameters of the model. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses neural networks to compute the word representations. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with visual data, but the techniques used in the paper may be applicable to image captioning tasks.
